!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

improper /ɪmˈprɒpə/

1. ADJ Improper activities are illegal or dishonest. 不合法的; 不诚实的 [正式] 

例： 25 officers were investigated following allegations of improper conduct. 25名警官被指控行为不当而受到调查。 

2. improperly ADV 不合法地; 不诚实地 [ADV with v] 

例： I acted neither fraudulently nor improperly. 我既未欺诈又未犯法。 

3. ADJ Improper conditions or methods of treatment are not suitable or good enough for a particular purpose. 不适当的 [正式] [ADJ n] 

例： The improper use of medicine could lead to severe adverse reactions. 用药不当会引起严重的不良反应。 

4. improperly ADV 不适当地 [ADV with v] 

例： The study confirmed many reports that doctors were improperly trained. 该研究证实了许多关于医生培训不足的报导。 

5. ADJ If you describe someone's behaviour as improper , you mean it is rude or shocking or in some way socially unacceptable. 不得体的 

例： Such improper behaviour and language from a young lady left me momentarily incapable of speech. 如此不得体的言行竟来自一位年轻女士，这让我惊愕得一时无语。 

6. improperly ADV 不得体地 [ADV with v] 

例： The company turns down people who show up at job interviews improperly dressed. 该公司拒绝那些在面试时衣着不得体的人。

</div>

